      "source": [
        "# Compressing ML Models for Edge Deployment with TensorFlow Lite\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "In this lab you will:\n",
        "\n",
        "1. load the **Fashion MNIST** dataset  \n",
        "2. train a small CNN baseline model  \n",
        "3. evaluate its **accuracy**, **size**, and **inference latency**  \n",
        "4. convert it to **TensorFlow Lite**  \n",
        "5. apply **dynamic range quantization**  \n",
        "6. apply **full integer quantization**  \n",
        "7. compare the trade-offs\n",
        "\n",
        "---\n",
        "\n",
        "## Why this matters in Industry 4.0\n",
        "\n",
        "In industrial environments, AI models often run **close to the machine**, not only in the cloud.  \n",
        "Examples include:\n",
        "\n",
        "- smart cameras for quality inspection\n",
        "- embedded sensors and gateways\n",
        "- predictive maintenance devices\n",
        "- edge controllers with limited memory and compute power\n",
        "\n",
        "In these scenarios, **model size**, **latency**, and **energy usage** matter a lot.  \n",
        "Compression techniques such as **quantization** help make ML models smaller and more efficient.\n"
      ]
    },
