      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "## Simple Numerical Example (Calibration)\n",
        "\n",
        "Suppose we have a small set of real values (e.g., from a representative dataset):\n",
        "\n",
        "`x = [-1.0, -0.5, 0.0, 0.2, 0.5, 0.9, 1.2, 1.5, 1.8, 2.0]`\n",
        "\n",
        "### Step 1: Find range\n",
        "- `min = -1.0`\n",
        "- `max = 2.0`\n",
        "\n",
        "### Step 2: Choose integer range (int8)\n",
        "- int8 range: `[-128, 127]`\n",
        "\n",
        "### Step 3: Compute scale\n",
        "\n",
        "$$\\text{scale} = \\frac{\\text{max} - \\text{min}}{127 - (-128)} = \\frac{2.0 - (-1.0)}{255} = \\frac{3.0}{255} \\approx 0.0118$$\n",
        "\n",
        "### Step 4: Compute zero-point\n",
        "\n",
        "$$\\text{zero_point} = -128 - \\frac{\\text{min}}{\\text{scale}} = -128 - \\frac{-1.0}{0.0118} \\approx -128 + 84.7 \\approx -43$$\n",
        "\n",
        "(rounded to nearest integer)\n",
        "\n",
        "---\n",
        "\n",
        "### Step 5: Quantize a value\n",
        "\n",
        "Take `x = 1.0`:\n",
        "\n",
        "$$q = \\frac{1.0}{0.0118} + (-43) \\approx 84.7 - 43 \\approx 42$$\n",
        "\n",
        "---\n",
        "\n",
        "### Step 6: Dequantize (check)\n",
        "\n",
        "$$x \\approx 0.0118 \\cdot (42 - (-43)) = 0.0118 \\cdot 85 \\approx 1.0$$\n",
        "\n",
        "---\n",
        "\n",
        "### Key Idea\n",
        "\n",
        "- We map real values in `[-1.0, 2.0]` to integers in `[-128, 127]`\n",
        "- **Scale** controls the step size\n",
        "- **Zero-point** aligns zero correctly\n",
        "- Small rounding errors are expected"
      ],
