        "## Edge vs Cloud Inference: Summary and Trade-offs\n",
        "\n",
        "In this lab, we explored how a machine learning model can be trained on a standard computing platform and then deployed on a highly resource-constrained device such as an ESP32-S3 microcontroller. This allows us to reason about the trade-offs between **edge inference** and **cloud-based inference**.\n",
        "\n",
        "### Model Compression and Deployment\n",
        "\n",
        "To run a model on a microcontroller, we applied **quantization** (e.g., from `float32` to `int8`), which significantly reduces:\n",
        "\n",
        "- memory footprint (≈4× smaller)\n",
        "- computational cost\n",
        "- energy consumption\n",
        "\n",
        "This makes it feasible to execute inference on devices with limited RAM and storage, while maintaining acceptable accuracy.\n",
        "\n",
        "However, this comes at a cost:\n",
        "\n",
        "- reduced numerical precision\n",
        "- need for simpler architectures\n",
        "- increased engineering effort (e.g., operator compatibility, memory management)\n",
        "\n",
        "---\n",
        "\n",
        "### Computational Performance\n",
        "\n",
        "We observed that:\n",
        "\n",
        "- **PC inference time**: ~0.095 ms  \n",
        "- **ESP32 inference time**: ~1.22 ms  \n",
        "\n",
        "This corresponds to:\n",
        "\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\\text{slowdown} \\approx 13\\times\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\n",
        "The microcontroller is slower because it has:\n",
        "\n",
        "- lower clock frequency\n",
        "- limited parallelism\n",
        "- no hardware acceleration comparable to CPUs/GPUs\n",
        "\n",
        "Thus, **edge devices are slower in raw computation** compared to desktop or server hardware.\n",
        "\n",
        "---\n",
        "\n",
        "### Cloud Inference Latency Model\n",
        "\n",
        "When using cloud inference, the total latency is not just computation time, but:\n",
        "\n",
        "$$\n",
        "T_{\\text{cloud}} =\n",
        "T_{\\text{upload}} +\n",
        "T_{\\text{network}} +\n",
        "T_{\\text{server}} +\n",
        "T_{\\text{download}}\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\n",
        "For small inputs like MNIST (≈1–3 KB per request), transmission time is negligible:\n",
        "\n",
        "$$\n",
        "T_{\\text{upload}} \\approx 1\\text{–}2 \\text{ ms}, \\quad\n",
        "T_{\\text{download}} \\approx <1 \\text{ ms}\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\n",
        "The dominant factor is **network latency (RTT)**:\n",
        "\n",
        "- local/fast network: 20–30 ms  \n",
        "- typical internet: 40–70 ms  \n",
        "- mobile/congested: 100+ ms  \n",
        "\n",
        "Even with fast server inference (~1 ms), total cloud latency typically becomes:\n",
        "\n",
        "$$\n",
        "T_{\\text{cloud}} \\approx 25\\text{–}120 \\text{ ms}\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\n",
        "---\n",
        "\n",
        "### Edge vs Cloud: Practical Comparison\n",
        "\n",
        "| Aspect              | Edge (ESP32)     | Cloud Inference        |\n",
        "|--------------------|------------------|------------------------|\n",
        "| Compute time       | ~1.22 ms         | ~0.095 ms (server)         |\n",
        "| Total latency      | ~1–2 ms          | ~25–120 ms             |\n",
        "| Model size         | Small, optimized | Large, flexible        |\n",
        "| Connectivity       | Not required     | Required               |\n",
        "| Privacy            | High             | Lower                  |\n",
        "| Scalability        | Limited          | High                   |\n",
        "\n",
        "---\n",
        "\n",
        "### Key Insight\n",
        "\n",
        "Although edge devices are **slower in raw computation**, they can be **faster in end-to-end latency** because they avoid network overhead.\n",
        "\n",
        "> Edge inference trades computational power for reduced latency, improved privacy, and independence from network connectivity.\n",
        "\n",
        "---\n",
        "\n",
        "### Takeaway\n",
        "\n",
        "- **Edge inference** is preferable when:\n",
